1
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:49,700
I baptize you

2
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:52,233
in the name of the Father,

3
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:54,133
and of the Son,

4
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:58,367
and of the Holy Spirit,

5
00:00:58,433 --> 00:00:59,467
Amen.

6
00:01:47,967 --> 00:01:49,400
Hi!

7
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:29,767
What?

8
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:37,133
- Congrats.
- Thank you.

9
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:40,133
- Congrats.
- Congrats.

10
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:43,433
Thank you, Emma, for agreeing
to be her godmother.

11
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:45,667
How can I say no
to your baby?

12
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:47,800
She's so beautiful.

13
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:51,033
Are you excited? You're next.

14
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:54,333
She definitely is.
Emma's so excited.

15
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,033
Every corner of our house
is full of baby stuff.

16
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:58,867
I have nowhere to go.

17
00:02:58,933 --> 00:03:02,267
Of course, we should be ready
for Kayla's arrival.

18
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:04,100
Of course.

19
00:03:04,167 --> 00:03:08,300
Your child is such a blessing
in your life.

20
00:03:08,367 --> 00:03:12,167
I thank God for listening
to my prayer.

21
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:14,200
- So, we'll go ahead, okay?
- Okay, stay safe, Emma.

22
00:03:14,267 --> 00:03:16,767
- All right, Nora. Congrats.
- Thank you, thank you.

23
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:18,367
- Thank you.
- Congrats again.

24
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,300
Hello Jeremy

25
00:03:24,367 --> 00:03:26,833
What do you mean
you can't make it?

26
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:30,100
Didn't you say we'd meet here
so it would be neutral grounds?

27
00:03:30,167 --> 00:03:32,867
Olive, stop calling me.
We're over.

28
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:34,667
What do you mean?

29
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:37,000
How about our child?

30
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:39,667
That baby is a mistake.

31
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:42,467
This baby is a blessing to me.

32
00:03:42,533 --> 00:03:44,700
Don't ruin my marriage.

33
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:47,400
Jeremy, please.

34
00:03:47,467 --> 00:03:50,367
You said you'll take
responsibility for us.

35
00:03:51,467 --> 00:03:53,400
I gave up many things for you.

36
00:03:53,467 --> 00:03:55,100
I even dropped out
of med school for you.

37
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,133
And this is what
you'll do in return?

38
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,500
Jeremy, answer me! Jeremy!

39
00:04:09,267 --> 00:04:10,933
Be careful.

40
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,067
I'm not injured.

41
00:04:15,933 --> 00:04:20,300
I know, but the doctor said
we should always be careful.

42
00:04:20,367 --> 00:04:23,733
You're supposed to be resting
at home right now.

43
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:26,967
But the doctor also said that...

44
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:29,433
it was unlikely for me
to have a miscarriage

45
00:04:29,533 --> 00:04:31,433
because we were already
in the third trimester.

46
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:34,867
Yes, Emma, but we should
still be careful,

47
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:39,067
so that our baby will be safe.

48
00:04:39,133 --> 00:04:41,833
I'm so lucky to have you.

49
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:45,233
Emma, I'm the one who's lucky.

50
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:47,033
I know,

51
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:49,267
I always ask you this...

52
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:54,100
but I really want
to marry you, Emma.

53
00:04:54,167 --> 00:04:57,700
We've been together
for a long time now.

54
00:04:57,767 --> 00:05:00,567
So that I could also prove
to our child,

55
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:03,233
that I will never
leave the both of you,

56
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:05,467
That I am responsible
for both of you, Emma.

57
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:10,233
I've wanted that
for a long time, too.

58
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:14,467
But maybe we should just wait
for Kayla to arrive.

59
00:05:14,533 --> 00:05:16,133
Because I want her
to be with us

60
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:18,333
when we take our vows
before God.

61
00:05:25,233 --> 00:05:27,167
- Let's go?
- Let's go.

62
00:05:41,633 --> 00:05:43,100
Angela, my dear...

63
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:47,967
don't listen to what
your dad is saying,

64
00:05:48,033 --> 00:05:50,533
that's not true.

65
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:53,900
You're the most beautiful thing
that happened in my life.

66
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:58,100
That's why don't
listen to him, okay?

67
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:04,433
You are so precious to me,
dear Angela.

68
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:27,000
- The child!
- Oh, no! The kid!

69
00:06:33,067 --> 00:06:38,367
- The child! The child!
- Oh, no! The kid!

70
00:06:38,433 --> 00:06:41,500
Hold on, hold on.
You're still at the church.

71
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:44,400
Hey!

72
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,500
What are you doing?
Why are holding my daughter?

73
00:06:48,567 --> 00:06:50,333
Wait, wait miss...

74
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,733
No...

75
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,567
are you trying to abduct
my daughter?

76
00:06:53,633 --> 00:06:56,000
What? We're abducting?

77
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:57,800
Hold on miss,
you are mistaken.

78
00:06:57,867 --> 00:06:59,400
We are actually saving
your daughter.

79
00:06:59,467 --> 00:07:02,200
You probably didn't notice that
the stroller moved over here.

80
00:07:02,267 --> 00:07:04,067
It almost got hit by a car.

81
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:05,967
What are you saying?

82
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:07,833
I didn't see anything.

83
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:10,700
Maybe you took my child
when I wasn't looking.

84
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,000
Stop making us
the bad guys here.

85
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:17,567
You should watch over your kid.
She almost had an accident.

86
00:07:17,633 --> 00:07:20,767
Don't you dare tell me
how to raise my daughter.

87
00:07:26,667 --> 00:07:28,233
Look at her, she's so rude.

88
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:31,900
She has the guts to do that
after we saved her daughter.

89
00:07:31,967 --> 00:07:35,267
I hope nothing bad happens
to the child.

90
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:37,233
I hope so, too, Emma.

91
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:39,300
Are you okay?

92
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:40,333
Let's go.

93
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:06,267
Emma!

94
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,733
Dan!

95
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:11,533
Are you finished with that?

96
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,000
Your timing is great,
I'm actually done with laundry.

97
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:16,167
Come on. I'll help you get up.

98
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:22,433
- Careful. Wait, wait.
- Okay.

99
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:23,767
Go ahead.

100
00:08:26,367 --> 00:08:27,633
Slowly, it's rocky.

101
00:08:28,767 --> 00:08:29,800
There.

102
00:08:31,767 --> 00:08:33,467
Dear!

103
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:35,200
Hi!

104
00:08:35,267 --> 00:08:39,300
I went to your house.
I'm glad I saw you here.

105
00:08:39,367 --> 00:08:42,267
- Mom.
- You're a pretty pregnant lady.

106
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,467
You really took after me.

107
00:08:44,533 --> 00:08:46,233
My dear...

108
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:49,667
do you have two thousand pesos?

109
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:50,833
Mom.

110
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:54,133
What will you do
with two thousand pesos?

111
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,633
It's because...

112
00:08:55,733 --> 00:09:00,000
my friends and I will go out.
I have no money.

113
00:09:00,067 --> 00:09:01,700
Look at my wallet.

114
00:09:01,767 --> 00:09:04,100
Are you going
to gamble again?

115
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:07,067
Hey! Come on. I've stopped
doing that a long time ago.

116
00:09:07,133 --> 00:09:09,733
Please, dear.
You're so pretty, dear.

117
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:15,433
Mom. You know that Danilo and I
are saving. Right?

118
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:20,733
All the money we save
is for Kayla.

119
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:24,433
Why did you even get pregnant
if you don't have enough money?

120
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:28,833
It's so expensive to raise
a child, and you're not married.

121
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:31,933
That's why I'm working
to save money, Mom.

122
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,333
For my family, for Emma
and our child.

123
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,200
Do you think that
would be enough?

124
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:38,833
How much do you make?

125
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:40,633
Emma...

126
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:43,633
why did you get a boyfriend
who's poorer than a rat?

127
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:46,400
How will you have a better life?

128
00:09:46,467 --> 00:09:50,767
Mom, don't talk
like that about Danilo.

129
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:53,100
He's a good man.

130
00:09:53,167 --> 00:09:55,467
He has a decent job.

131
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:57,933
And we're doing everything

132
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:02,600
to give our child, Kayla,
a better future.

133
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:04,233
I hope so.

134
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,833
Fine, I'll ask someone else.

135
00:10:10,367 --> 00:10:12,200
Just let it slide.

136
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:14,467
Just ignore your mom.

137
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,633
Let's go.

138
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,100
Are you okay?

139
00:10:22,267 --> 00:10:24,533
That's okay, my love.

140
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,033
Are you finished? Okay.

141
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,467
The event is about to start.

142
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:32,933
Hold on. I'm still feeding
baby Angela.

143
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,800
Where's her nanny?

144
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:40,033
She left last night.

145
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:41,933
She and the driver.

146
00:10:48,433 --> 00:10:51,133
How many times has your
nanny abandoned you?

147
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:55,000
Maybe you're too strict.

148
00:10:55,067 --> 00:10:57,233
You can say whatever you want.

149
00:10:57,300 --> 00:11:00,067
I only want what's best
for Angela.

150
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,667
Let's go.

151
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,433
Hold on.

152
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:17,433
Is that...

153
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,067
don't even ask.

154
00:11:19,133 --> 00:11:21,300
I need this.

155
00:11:21,367 --> 00:11:22,633
Hi, everyone!

156
00:11:23,667 --> 00:11:24,900
Thank you so much for coming

157
00:11:24,967 --> 00:11:27,733
to the grand opening
of Artemis Pharmacy.

158
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:30,600
Because of your continued
support and patronage,

159
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:32,533
we have become the number one

160
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:35,000
and fastest-growing
pharmaceutical chain

161
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:36,767
here in the region.

162
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:39,833
And as my parents promised,

163
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,933
I will continue this business

164
00:11:42,033 --> 00:11:44,200
even though they're
no longer here.

165
00:11:44,267 --> 00:11:47,700
I am doing this
in honor of them.

166
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:53,133
And for my beautiful baby
daughter, Maria Angela.

167
00:11:56,533 --> 00:11:58,833
Thank you. Thank you.

168
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:04,200
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Come in.

169
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:05,600
Enjoy.

170
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:10,633
Where are you going?

171
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:12,200
You still have
a press interview.

172
00:12:12,267 --> 00:12:14,033
No, Astrid. I have to go.

173
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,033
Why?

174
00:12:15,133 --> 00:12:16,667
You're the president
of Artemis Pharmacy.

175
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:18,100
You have to be here.

176
00:12:18,167 --> 00:12:20,100
My friend called me.

177
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:23,433
She saw Jeremy at the airport
with his family.

178
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:25,033
I need to see him.

179
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:27,500
The airport is far from here,
it's in Manila.

180
00:12:27,567 --> 00:12:29,233
And even if you catch him,

181
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:32,033
are you sure
that you can you stop him?

182
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,267
What do you want
me to do, Astrid?

183
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:37,133
To just sit here
and not do anything?

184
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:40,100
He's with his wife and child.

185
00:12:40,167 --> 00:12:41,833
Clearly, he's made up his mind.

186
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:44,100
Why don't you just let him go?

187
00:12:44,167 --> 00:12:45,333
No.

188
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,500
I am doing this for my daughter.

189
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,800
I want baby Angela
to grow up with a father.

190
00:12:50,867 --> 00:12:53,600
- Leave Maria Angela to me.
- No!

191
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:55,800
I need to bring
Maria Angela with me.

192
00:12:55,867 --> 00:12:57,867
I'll show her to Jeremy.

193
00:12:57,933 --> 00:13:01,433
Just in case he changes
his mind and goes back to us.

194
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:03,067
Okay, Olive. I'll drive for you.

195
00:13:03,133 --> 00:13:04,200
No, no, no. You stay here.

196
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:05,767
Take care of the opening, okay?

197
00:13:05,833 --> 00:13:08,033
Take care of the press
and everyone there.

198
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,900
And once this is done,
just go home.

199
00:13:09,967 --> 00:13:11,100
But...

200
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:15,000
I'm sorry about what Mom did.

201
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:17,867
Forget about it.

202
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:19,333
I'm already used to your mom.

203
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:22,167
No matter what she says,

204
00:13:22,267 --> 00:13:24,700
it just goes in one ear
and out the other.

205
00:13:24,767 --> 00:13:26,100
I no longer get affected.

206
00:13:26,167 --> 00:13:27,933
It's okay. Don't worry.

207
00:13:29,133 --> 00:13:30,667
You know,

208
00:13:30,733 --> 00:13:35,633
If Mom thinks that this child
will be a burden to us,

209
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:37,233
that's not true.

210
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:42,467
Because I've been praying
for a child for a long time.

211
00:13:42,533 --> 00:13:46,433
And you'll be the best mother.

212
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:47,567
Because our future child

213
00:13:47,633 --> 00:13:49,467
will be so lucky
to have you as her mom.

214
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:55,500
Right, baby Kayla?

215
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:02,233
Angela, please!

216
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:03,700
Please stop crying!

217
00:14:05,867 --> 00:14:07,733
What do you need, dear?

218
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,367
Are you hungry?

219
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:12,833
What's the problem?
Are you not feeling well?

220
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:15,933
Please stop crying.
I'm already panicking.

221
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:18,533
Ouch.

222
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:21,267
- Why?
- Dan, my tummy aches.

223
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:23,000
I can't explain.

224
00:14:23,067 --> 00:14:24,667
I think I'm already
giving birth.

225
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:27,500
This is all your father's fault!

226
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:32,533
I don't know why he left and
chose his family over us.

227
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:38,300
Doesn't he know how difficult
it is to raise a child alone?

228
00:14:38,367 --> 00:14:39,800
Come on. I'll bring you
to the hospital.

229
00:14:39,867 --> 00:14:41,567
- Let's go.
- Ouch!

230
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:43,033
It hurts!

231
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:47,367
Mommy's here for you, okay?

232
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:49,767
You and Mommy forever.

233
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:52,633
Dan, it hurts!

234
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:55,967
Ouch! Dear, wait. Ouch.

235
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:58,800
Stop crying, Angela. Please.

236
00:14:58,867 --> 00:15:01,133
Stop.

237
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,467
There's a car
in front of us!

238
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,467
No!

239
00:15:23,533 --> 00:15:27,433
No!

240
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:29,800
Angela!

241
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:31,100
My child!

242
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:32,767
Help!

243
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:35,067
Please help us!

244
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:39,933
Angela!

245
00:15:42,833 --> 00:15:45,100
There she is.

246
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:46,300
Our child is coming out.
There she is.

247
00:15:46,367 --> 00:15:47,833
Our daughter has come out.

248
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,100
Doc?

249
00:16:09,533 --> 00:16:11,800
Where are you
bringing our child?

250
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:13,267
The baby is premature.

251
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:17,133
That's why we need to transfer
her to NICU for monitoring.

252
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,500
What?

253
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,900
Angela?

254
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:45,667
- Angela?
- Olive?

255
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,633
Olive?

256
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:49,433
Olive, I'm glad
you're awake now.

257
00:16:54,133 --> 00:16:56,500
Where's my daughter?

258
00:16:56,567 --> 00:17:00,067
- Olive?
- My daughter.

259
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:01,833
Where's Angela?

260
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:04,533
Olive, I'm sorry.

261
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:07,267
- What?
- Olive, I'm sorry.

262
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:08,500
No.

263
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:14,467
- I'm so sorry.
- No! No!

264
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:24,500
No!

265
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:30,200
No!

266
00:17:30,267 --> 00:17:32,233
- No!
- Olive, I'm sorry.

267
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:33,867
My child!

268
00:17:33,933 --> 00:17:39,300
Give me my child! No!

269
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:45,100
Hello.

270
00:17:45,167 --> 00:17:47,033
- Hi, Emma.
- Doc.

271
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:49,400
Doc. How's my child?

272
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:53,367
Emma, we need to put
your child in NICU

273
00:17:53,433 --> 00:17:58,300
because we saw signs
of infection or sepsis.

274
00:17:58,367 --> 00:17:59,400
Is that dangerous?

275
00:17:59,467 --> 00:18:00,867
If it is not treated promptly

276
00:18:00,933 --> 00:18:03,333
and given the correct
medication,

277
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:05,600
the child can die from it

278
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:06,667
What?

279
00:18:06,733 --> 00:18:08,033
Doc.

280
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:10,500
How did she get that?

281
00:18:10,567 --> 00:18:13,367
It's possible that she got it
when she was born.

282
00:18:13,433 --> 00:18:15,600
And because the baby
is pre-term,

283
00:18:15,667 --> 00:18:17,633
her immune system
may not be able to handle

284
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:19,867
such an infection yet.

285
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:21,967
But, Emma, don't worry.

286
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:24,933
We're going to do everything
to save your child.

287
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:30,800
For now, we need to make the
baby's immune system strong.

288
00:18:30,867 --> 00:18:32,133
You must regain
your strength, too, Emma.

289
00:18:33,633 --> 00:18:34,933
Thank you. I'll get going.

290
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,333
- Excuse me.
- Thank you.

291
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,433
What if...

292
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:49,967
what if Kayla can't handle it?

293
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:53,867
What if her
body's still weak?

294
00:18:53,933 --> 00:18:57,867
Dan, I can't bear
to lose another child.

295
00:18:57,967 --> 00:18:59,200
Mom.

296
00:18:59,267 --> 00:19:00,633
Don't worry.

297
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,967
God has mercy.

298
00:19:03,033 --> 00:19:05,533
The doctor said you must
regain your strength.

299
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:31,200
Emma.

300
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,800
I've talked to the doctor.

301
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:37,933
Baby Kayla needs an antibiotic.

302
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:42,533
She'll be given medicine three
times a day for two weeks.

303
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:43,967
What?

304
00:19:44,033 --> 00:19:47,467
Does it mean she'll stay
here for another two weeks?

305
00:19:47,533 --> 00:19:54,233
If that's what we need
for Kayla to get better.

306
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:58,967
But the hospital doesn't have
the medicine that Kayla needs.

307
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:01,033
We have to buy it outside.

308
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:03,733
She needs 5,000 pesos, Mom.

309
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,333
5,000 pesos for a single dose?

310
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,000
Three times a week?

311
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:08,500
That means 15,000 pesos?

312
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:10,933
Two weeks...

313
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:14,200
that's 70,000 pesos!

314
00:20:14,267 --> 00:20:15,267
- But...
- where will you get

315
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,467
such a hefty amount of money?

316
00:20:17,533 --> 00:20:19,600
No matter how expensive,

317
00:20:19,667 --> 00:20:22,700
I will do it even if I have to
sell all my belongings.

318
00:20:22,767 --> 00:20:23,567
Even if I have to knock
on the door

319
00:20:23,633 --> 00:20:25,033
of every person I know
for help,

320
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:29,200
I will do it just to save Kayla.
We can't lose her.

321
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:37,533
Dear,

322
00:20:39,233 --> 00:20:41,100
I promise you.

323
00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:43,900
Your dad and I will
get you out of here.

324
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:51,500
We'll do everything
to treat you.

325
00:20:51,567 --> 00:20:54,033
Dear, hang in there, okay?

326
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:21,833
Why is it that everyone
I love is leaving me?

327
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:26,433
What kind of curse is this?

328
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:30,967
I'm so angry.

329
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:35,633
The only thing

330
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:39,000
that can rid me
of this searing pain

331
00:21:42,333 --> 00:21:44,800
is if I can be
with Angela again.

332
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:50,600
If I'm given a second chance,

333
00:21:56,067 --> 00:21:57,800
I will do anything...

334
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:03,300
just to get my daughter back.

335
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:14,667
How much can we buy
from that money?

336
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:18,467
Two bottles only.

337
00:22:18,533 --> 00:22:20,467
Just two bottles?

338
00:22:20,533 --> 00:22:21,400
What do we do?

339
00:22:21,467 --> 00:22:24,500
Baby Kayla needs
three bottles per day.

340
00:22:24,567 --> 00:22:25,400
That's not enough.

341
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:27,733
Isn't there anything
cheaper, Miss?

342
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:28,633
A generic one?

343
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:30,767
This is all we have.

344
00:22:42,967 --> 00:22:46,800
I really hate going
to this hospital.

345
00:22:46,867 --> 00:22:50,733
You need to have your injuries
checked by a doctor.

346
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:53,400
Every time I come here,

347
00:22:53,467 --> 00:22:56,100
I remember what happened
to my daughter.

348
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:59,600
It's like my conscience
is killing me.

349
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:04,000
Olive,

350
00:23:05,533 --> 00:23:08,133
do you really not want
to talk to a therapist?

351
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:11,067
To help you process
your grief.

352
00:23:14,433 --> 00:23:17,067
Do you honestly believe

353
00:23:17,133 --> 00:23:20,167
that talking to a therapist
will bring my daughter back?

354
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:24,067
That's important
for your mental health.

355
00:23:30,733 --> 00:23:31,867
Excuse me.

356
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:34,933
Hello?

357
00:23:37,367 --> 00:23:38,400
Yes?

358
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:43,433
We just need to take care
of the documents, maybe...

359
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,667
tomorrow?

360
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:48,300
Okay. What else is needed?

361
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:08,533
Olive, what are you doing?

362
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:12,900
I'm just staring at this baby.

363
00:24:15,267 --> 00:24:16,300
Look.

364
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:20,200
She looks so adorable.

365
00:24:21,233 --> 00:24:24,633
Look at that cute little
heart-shaped birthmark.

366
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:31,467
I remember Angela in her.

367
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:03,700
Don't worry about it. It's okay.

368
00:25:03,767 --> 00:25:04,933
But thank you.

369
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:08,000
- I'll get going.
- Bye.

370
00:25:11,367 --> 00:25:14,867
We've sold almost everything,

371
00:25:14,933 --> 00:25:16,500
but it's still not enough.

372
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:21,067
I only get a little
government assistance.

373
00:25:21,133 --> 00:25:23,267
Dan, don't worry.

374
00:25:23,333 --> 00:25:24,600
I'll go to Manila tomorrow.

375
00:25:24,667 --> 00:25:27,233
I'll borrow money
from my employer.

376
00:25:27,300 --> 00:25:29,100
We can do this, okay?

377
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:36,967
How can you pay me?

378
00:25:37,067 --> 00:25:41,333
Ma'am, I promise once my
daughter is out of the hospital,

379
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:45,200
I'll work for the money
I owe you.

380
00:25:45,267 --> 00:25:47,267
I'll do everything.

381
00:25:47,333 --> 00:25:50,000
I'll do the laundry
and mop the floor.

382
00:25:50,067 --> 00:25:53,733
I'll do everything
you tell me to.

383
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,733
I'm sorry, Emma.

384
00:25:58,867 --> 00:26:00,867
I still don't have
money to lend you.

385
00:26:05,133 --> 00:26:06,667
Ma'am.

386
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:11,100
I'll be shameless.

387
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:15,333
I have no one else
to ask for help,

388
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:17,500
only you.

389
00:26:17,567 --> 00:26:21,567
I just really need to buy
my child's medicine

390
00:26:21,633 --> 00:26:26,600
so she can live longer.

391
00:26:26,667 --> 00:26:28,867
Ma'am, please help me.

392
00:26:28,933 --> 00:26:34,067
Please help us, Ma'am.
Please help my daughter.

393
00:26:34,133 --> 00:26:37,100
Ma'am, I am begging you.

394
00:27:06,733 --> 00:27:08,633
Finally, my dear.

395
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:11,400
I can hold you and hug you.

396
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:14,567
I told you, didn't I?

397
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:16,200
Your dad and
I will do everything

398
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:19,267
for you to get well.

399
00:27:19,333 --> 00:27:21,900
We still need
to thank your employer.

400
00:27:21,967 --> 00:27:24,033
You know, maybe...

401
00:27:24,100 --> 00:27:26,667
this is just
a test from God.

402
00:27:26,733 --> 00:27:30,167
Maybe He wants to see how ready
we are to be parents.

403
00:27:30,233 --> 00:27:34,200
But we've proven it, Emma.

404
00:27:34,267 --> 00:27:38,000
That we can do everything
for our child.

405
00:27:39,067 --> 00:27:40,900
Every day,

406
00:27:40,967 --> 00:27:46,200
Your dad and I will thank
God for giving you to us.

407
00:27:46,267 --> 00:27:49,900
We will never waste
our second chance.

408
00:27:54,833 --> 00:27:56,167
Let's go.

409
00:28:37,467 --> 00:28:41,433
- Our daughter is so cute.
- Dear.

410
00:28:41,500 --> 00:28:43,500
She's so behave.

411
00:28:43,567 --> 00:28:46,400
- She's sleeping soundly.
- She's so beautiful.

412
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:53,167
Let's fix this.

413
00:28:53,233 --> 00:28:55,100
My daughter is so beautiful.

414
00:29:04,167 --> 00:29:05,700
There it is. Let's go, Emma.

415
00:29:35,567 --> 00:29:39,167
Let me carry my super
cute granddaughter.

416
00:29:39,233 --> 00:29:41,767
Baby Kayla.

417
00:29:41,833 --> 00:29:45,000
What a beautiful baby!

418
00:29:45,067 --> 00:29:47,200
Such a pretty baby!

419
00:29:47,267 --> 00:29:49,767
- Who does she look like?
- Dan.

420
00:29:49,833 --> 00:29:51,767
- Who does she look like?
- Dan, here are the...

421
00:29:51,833 --> 00:29:54,167
- do you look like your dad?
- There are some diapers

422
00:29:54,233 --> 00:29:55,433
here for Kayla.

423
00:29:55,500 --> 00:29:58,133
Change her diaper once it gets
full, she might get rashes.

424
00:29:58,200 --> 00:29:58,933
- Okay?
- Okay.

425
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:00,800
Do you hear me... Dan?

426
00:30:00,867 --> 00:30:02,433
- Yes.
- Dan, do you hear me?

427
00:30:02,533 --> 00:30:03,933
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

428
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:06,233
I'll take care of our child.
Let me have that.

429
00:30:07,867 --> 00:30:10,000
- It's because...
- I'll put it here.

430
00:30:10,067 --> 00:30:12,800
I don't want to leave.

431
00:30:12,867 --> 00:30:15,867
I don't want to return to work
because Kayla's still little.

432
00:30:15,933 --> 00:30:20,100
But I need to pay our debt.

433
00:30:23,733 --> 00:30:26,000
Dear.

434
00:30:26,067 --> 00:30:27,933
Keep this with you always.

435
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,100
Even though I'm not with you,

436
00:30:30,167 --> 00:30:32,433
you can remember me.

437
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:35,600
Whenever you have this cloth,

438
00:30:35,700 --> 00:30:41,000
you'll feel I'm always
by your side.

439
00:30:41,067 --> 00:30:45,067
Mom, can I carry my
daughter before I go?

440
00:30:45,133 --> 00:30:46,433
There you go.

441
00:30:46,500 --> 00:30:50,467
- Go to your mom.
- Baby Kayla.

442
00:30:50,533 --> 00:30:53,167
- Thank you, Mom.
- Okay.

443
00:30:56,267 --> 00:31:00,500
Stop crying, dear.

444
00:31:00,567 --> 00:31:05,300
Stay with me.

445
00:31:05,367 --> 00:31:12,700
Sleep among the stars.

446
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:16,833
I won't leave you.

447
00:31:16,900 --> 00:31:20,833
You won't get hurt.

448
00:31:20,900 --> 00:31:28,467
You are always safe with me.

449
00:31:28,533 --> 00:31:38,500
And I promise you I will love
you for the rest of my life.

450
00:31:42,267 --> 00:31:45,333
Bye!

451
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:48,433
There.

452
00:31:48,500 --> 00:31:50,667
Dad will take care of you.

453
00:31:50,733 --> 00:31:52,667
Yes. Don't cry.

454
00:31:52,733 --> 00:31:55,600
Let's go. Let's go inside.

455
00:31:55,667 --> 00:31:57,100
The weather is bad.

456
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:08,367
The typhoon has strengthened
into a severe tropical storm...

457
00:32:08,433 --> 00:32:11,367
signal number 3
has been raised in the NCR

458
00:32:11,433 --> 00:32:15,567
and in the provinces
of Rizal, Laguna, and Cavite.

459
00:32:15,667 --> 00:32:20,000
It is expected to cause
flooding and landslides.

460
00:32:20,067 --> 00:32:30,033
It packs a maximum sustained
winds of 95 kilometers per hour.

461
00:32:34,433 --> 00:32:36,700
Save yourselves!

462
00:32:36,767 --> 00:32:38,933
Go to the evacuation center!

463
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:40,633
Go, my fellow citizens.

464
00:32:40,700 --> 00:32:42,067
What's going on?

465
00:32:42,133 --> 00:32:44,000
Didn't you hear our call?

466
00:32:44,067 --> 00:32:45,767
No. I'm taking care of my child.

467
00:32:45,833 --> 00:32:49,000
We're bringing the people
to the evacuation center!

468
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:50,867
Follow them!

469
00:32:50,933 --> 00:32:52,133
Danilo, move faster!

470
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,533
Okay, okay.
I'll just get my daughter.

471
00:32:57,633 --> 00:33:00,167
Rain continues to fall
in the Sierra Madre.

472
00:33:00,233 --> 00:33:03,933
Residents are currently
being evacuated.

473
00:33:20,300 --> 00:33:23,533
Danilo, why aren't you
answering the phone?

474
00:33:37,267 --> 00:33:39,700
According to the Disaster
and Risk Reduction

475
00:33:39,767 --> 00:33:40,833
Management office,

476
00:33:40,900 --> 00:33:42,967
nearly 20 houses were destroyed

477
00:33:43,033 --> 00:33:44,333
- by the landslide.
- Danillo.

478
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:47,367
It is also estimated that
up to 50 people

479
00:33:47,433 --> 00:33:50,633
- have been buried in the mud.
- Answer the phone.

480
00:33:59,767 --> 00:34:01,500
They didn't see a baby.

481
00:34:01,567 --> 00:34:04,433
Does it mean my granddaughter
is underneath the mud?

482
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:08,100
I can't lose my child.

483
00:34:08,167 --> 00:34:10,133
This is my fault.

484
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:12,200
I should have died instead!

485
00:34:12,267 --> 00:34:15,800
If you had only listened to me
and give Kayla up for adoption,

486
00:34:15,867 --> 00:34:17,300
this wouldn't happen.

487
00:34:17,367 --> 00:34:23,200
I've prayed for you to come into
our lives for so long.

488
00:34:23,267 --> 00:34:26,667
Why did we only have
you for a short while?

489
00:34:26,733 --> 00:34:30,567
Wherever you are now, I hope
you're in a better place.
